quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  39,48,"And the evil (consequences) of what they wrought shall become plain to them, and the very thing they mocked at shall beset them"
  39,49,"Now when harm afflicts a man he calls upon Us; then, when We give him a favour from Us, he says, \"I have been given it only by means of knowledge.\" Nay, it is a trial, but most of them know not"
  39,50,"Those before them did indeed say this, but what they earned availed them not"
  39,51,"But there befell them the evil (consequences) of what they earned; and those who are unjust from among this generation, there shall also befall them the evil (consequences) of what they earn, and they shall not escape"
  39,52,"Do they not know that Allah enlarges the means of subsistence to whom He wills, and He restricts; most surely there are signs in this for a people who believe"
  39,53,"Say, \"O my servants! Who have acted extravagantly (transgressed) against their own souls, do not despair of the mercy of Allah; surely Allah forgives all faults; surely He is the Forgiving the Merciful"
  39,54,And return to your Lord time after time and submit to Him before there come unto you the punishment when you cannot be helped
  39,55,And follow the best of that which has been revealed to you from your Lord before the punishment comes suddenly while you do not even perceive
  39,56,"Lest a soul should say, \"O woe to me! For what I fell short of my duty to Allah, and I was indeed among the scoffers"